text:
Shark Fact of the Day:

Most free-swimming sharks have a feature called counter-shading, where the top half of their body is coloured blue and the bottom half is coloured white. When viewed from above, a shark blends in with the surrounding water. When viewed from below, it's lost in the sunlight filtering down.

This means that such sharks are difficult to spot unless they're swimming at your eye level, so they're great at jump scares!
